description.narrative:
Front Line Defenders provides direct practical support for HRDs that is based directly on their articulated needs - including emergency funding. Front Line Defenders has a four year Strategic Plan covering the period 2019-2022 with the below presented four strategic goals / objectives, which interlink with Front Line Defenders' Theory of Change. 
The expected result on impact level for the intervention is: Human Right Defenders (HRDs) at the local and national level enjoy the freedom and security to undertake their legitimate activities. The expected result on outcome level is: Stronger international protection for human rights defenders to enable them to better manage their security and carry out their legitimate work - more HRDs at risk have received positive benefit of support for their legitimate work. The correlated 4 strategic objectives are:
(1) Provide fast, flexible and effective 24-hour emergency response that responds to the protection needs of HRDs at immediate risk;
(2) Strengthen the resilience and capacity of HRDs to manage their security and protection;
(3) Enhance the visibility of HRDs and the positive impact of their work;
(4) Strengthen national, regional and international protection of HRDs at risk.

The contribution is a core support on SEK 36 000 000 to the organisation Front Line Defenders for implementing their Strategic Plan during the period 2020-2022.

The overall goal is to enable human rights defenders (HRDs) at the local and national level enjoy the freedom and security to undertake their legitimate activities. The correlated 4 strategic objectives for the Strategic Plan are:

(1) Provide fast, flexible and effective 24-hour emergency response that responds to the protection needs of HRDs at immediate risk;

(2) Strengthen the resilience and capacity of HRDs to manage their security and protection;

(3) Enhance the visibility of HRDs and the positive impact of their work;

(4) Strengthen national, regional and international protection of HRDs at risk.
